I definitely think so, because `self.engine.match()` needs an instance of `pook.request.Request`.
My approach is extending the `Entry` class with something similar to the following lines:
```python
class MocketPookEntry(Entry):

    def can_handle(self, data):
        can_handle = super(MocketPookEntry, self).can_handle(data)

        if can_handle:
            pass  # call the self.engine.match() method
