@bpatelcs first - thanks for the issue!

I'm not entirely sure what you're suggesting. This particular form of the `__call__` function was adopted to fix #20. The root cause of this issue is the fact that decorators on class methods or globally scoped functions are evaluated at import time, not at runtime. So attributes passed into the `zipkin_span`'s `__init__` method might have incorrect values.

See https://github.com/Yelp/py_zipkin/pull/21 for the fix.

